An Act to protect animal health.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 129 of the general laws is hereby amended in section 27 by adding
2 at the end thereof the following new paragraph:
3 Each entity that is not otherwise required to be licensed under M.G.L. c. 129, §§ 39, 39A,
4 or 45, or under M.G.L. c. 94, § 152A, and whose primary activity is the placement of abandoned,
5 displaced, unwanted, neglected or abused animals and is exempt from taxation under § 501(c)(3)
6 of the federal Internal Revenue Code, or equivalent nonprofit designation under such Code, shall
7 report to the director on an annual basis the number of dogs and cats brought into the state during
8 the prior year by such entity and the state or country of origin for each such animal including, but
9 not limited to identification of the origination source and transporter. Such report shall be on a
10 form as prescribed by the director.
